-- Duratex Rises After First-Quarter Sales Exceed Analyst Estimates
-- B y   D e n y s e   G o d o y
-- 2013-04-23T15:39:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-23/duratex-rises-after-first-quarter-sales-exceed-analyst-estimates.html
Duratex SA (DTEX3) , a maker of wood panels
and metal fixtures including faucets, jumped after reporting
profit that exceeded analysts’ estimates.  The shares rose 2.5 percent to 14.68 reais at 11:49 a.m. in
Sao Paulo, the highest intraday price since April 12. The
benchmark Ibovespa gained 1 percent.  Duratex’s adjusted net income rose 63 percent to 140.6
million reais ($69.8 million) in the first quarter from a year
earlier, according to data compiled by Bloomberg after the Sao
Paulo-based company released results late yesterday. That
compares with an average estimate of 129.5 million reais among
four analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  The stock is the second-most favored on the  Ibovespa, (IBOV)  based
on a composite of analyst ratings compiled by Bloomberg.
Duratex’s  consensus rating  is 4.71, trailing only iron ore
mining company  Vale SA. (VALE5)   Duratex has advanced 8.6 percent this year while the
Ibovespa declined 10 percent during the same period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
